## Permitted Uses

You may use the Software for any purpose, including commercial purposes, provided
that you are not offering it as a managed hosting service to third parties.

Specifically, you may:

- Run the Software on your own infrastructure (local machine or VPS) for personal
  or internal business use.
- Modify the Software and contribute changes back to the project.
- Use the Software to conduct outreach and automation for your own business.
- Offer consulting, support, or integration services that involve the Software,
  as long as the Software itself is not the product being sold.

## Prohibited Uses

You may NOT:

- Offer the Software as a hosted or managed service to third parties — meaning
  you cannot provide access to a running instance of the Software to users who
  did not set it up themselves, in exchange for payment or free of charge.
- Sublicense the Software for managed hosting purposes.

**Exception:** Opsily (opsily.com) is the sole authorized managed hosting
provider for Linki. This exception is non-transferable.

